  <!-- EN: antibiotics addiction -->
  <VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.label>抗生素成瘾</VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.label>
  <!-- EN: A chemical addiction to antibiotics. Long-term presence of antibiotics has caused neurological adaptations at the cellular level, so the brain can no longer function properly without the drug.\n\nWithout regular doses of antibiotics, withdrawal symptoms will begin. However, extended abstinence will force the brain to adapt back to its normal state, resolving the addiction.-->
  <VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.description>长期过量的食用抗生素已经造成了神经系统的适应。\n\n如果没有定期食用合适数量的抗生素，戒断反应就会开始。长时间的戒断会迫使大脑适应并恢复到正常状态，从而戒除抗生素成瘾。</VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.description>
  <!-- EN: withdrawal -->
  <VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.stages.withdrawal.label>戒断</VRE_AntibioticsAddiction.stages.withdrawal.label>
  
  <!-- EN: antibiotics -->
  <VRE_AntibioticsHigh.label>抗生素</VRE_AntibioticsHigh.label>
  <!-- EN: A drug for boosting the immune system after infections take hold. Helps against diseases, such as malaria and plague, as well as infections due to unclean wounds. Lasts 12 hours. Effect is stronger depending on the severity of the immunity genes of the ingester (stronger for less immune subjects), and it is modified by the person's tolerance to the drug.-->
  <VRE_AntibioticsHigh.description>一种感染后增强免疫的药物。有助于预防疾病，如疟疾和瘟疫，以及不洁伤口引起的感染。持续12小时。药效会根据使用者免疫基因的等级而增强（对弱免疫基因的携带者效果会强），也会被该人的抗生素耐受所影响。</VRE_AntibioticsHigh.description>
  
